[APPLAUSE]

00:14:40.990 --> 00:14:45.930
KRISHNA DAS: So once again, the
instructions are very simple.

00:14:45.930 --> 00:14:47.100
You repeat.

00:14:47.100 --> 00:14:47.860
I sing a line.

00:14:47.860 --> 00:14:49.885
And then you all
sing something that

00:14:49.885 --> 00:14:52.260
sounds something like something
I might've sung sometime.

00:14:52.260 --> 00:14:54.040
[LAUGHTER]

00:14:54.040 --> 00:14:57.160
And then we keep
going back and forth.

00:14:57.160 --> 00:15:00.160
And when you notice that
you're not paying attention--

00:15:00.160 --> 00:15:01.630
don't try too hard.

00:15:01.630 --> 00:15:03.640
But when you notice you're
not paying attention,

00:15:03.640 --> 00:15:06.616
just simply come
back to the chanting.

00:15:06.616 --> 00:15:08.740
And you might sit here for
10 minutes just thinking

00:15:08.740 --> 00:15:11.110
about other stuff
until you notice

00:15:11.110 --> 00:15:12.820
that that's what you're doing.

00:15:12.820 --> 00:15:14.500
It's an amazing
moment, that moment

00:15:14.500 --> 00:15:19.600
when you notice that you've
been gone for x amount of time.

00:15:19.600 --> 00:15:22.270
It's a miracle that we
ever come back actually.

00:15:29.140 --> 00:15:32.260
We'll sing a chant, Shri
Ram Jay Ram Jay Jay Ram.

00:15:32.260 --> 00:15:34.700
It's in your hymnals, yeah.

00:15:34.700 --> 00:15:38.200
Shri Ram Jay Ram Jay Jay
Ram, and Sita Ram Sita Ram.

00:15:38.200 --> 00:15:39.160
So I'll sing a line.

00:15:39.160 --> 00:15:41.730
And then if you
like, you can answer.

00:15:41.730 --> 00:15:43.390
