00:35:56.859 --> 00:35:59.860
So shri ram jay.

00:35:59.860 --> 00:36:06.485
So do that for a few
days and see what's left.

00:36:06.485 --> 00:36:07.360
That's how I learned.

00:36:07.360 --> 00:36:08.777
My guru said start singing.

00:36:08.777 --> 00:36:10.360
He didn't say anything
about stopping.

00:36:10.360 --> 00:36:12.720
[LAUGHTER]

00:36:12.720 --> 00:36:17.500
After a few weeks,
it's like, hello.

00:36:17.500 --> 00:36:22.340
We can't think our way out of a
prison that's made of thought.

00:36:22.340 --> 00:36:25.290
We have to find some
other way of getting out

00:36:25.290 --> 00:36:30.530
of jail, the jail of
our obsessive thinking

00:36:30.530 --> 00:36:36.370
and our self-judgment
evaluation, constant, ongoing.

00:36:36.370 --> 00:36:38.720
It's what humans do.

00:36:38.720 --> 00:36:40.990
But it's very hard to
change that pattern.

00:36:40.990 --> 00:36:45.460
So you have to add
some other dimension.

00:36:45.460 --> 00:36:48.590
And that is simply paying
attention, coming back.

00:36:48.590 --> 00:36:50.740
And then you start to
recognize things from inside.

00:36:50.740 --> 00:36:52.990
And nobody has to tell you.

00:36:52.990 --> 00:36:55.410
Nobody can give this to you.

00:36:55.410 --> 00:36:57.370
Nobody has to turn you on.

00:36:57.370 --> 00:36:59.770
We're already turned on.

00:36:59.770 --> 00:37:02.180
We just to have to
uncover what's in there.

00:37:02.180 --> 00:37:04.840
And that's what
these practices do.

00:37:04.840 --> 00:37:08.540
All of them do the same thing.

00:37:08.540 --> 00:37:11.000
Slightly different angle,
they come at the same thing.

00:37:11.000 --> 00:37:11.916
But it's all the same.

00:37:14.180 --> 00:37:15.110
My guru used to go--

00:37:19.220 --> 00:37:20.370
no matter what.

00:37:20.370 --> 00:37:21.180
He knew everything.

00:37:21.180 --> 00:37:21.830
Right?

00:37:21.830 --> 00:37:22.940
Past, present, and future?

00:37:22.940 --> 00:37:25.760
So he'd look at
you and he'd go--

00:37:25.760 --> 00:37:27.170
what am I getting busted for?

00:37:27.170 --> 00:37:29.715
Something I did, something I'm
going to do, or something I'm

00:37:29.715 --> 00:37:30.590
thinking about doing?

00:37:30.590 --> 00:37:32.312
[LAUGHTER]

00:37:32.312 --> 00:37:34.520
So we said, Baba, what does
it mean when you do that?

00:37:34.520 --> 00:37:40.670
And he went-- like that.

00:37:40.670 --> 00:37:42.600
What does that mean?

00:37:42.600 --> 00:37:49.160
He said, many names, many
forms, all one, all one.

00:37:49.160 --> 00:37:54.840
So that's where he
lived, in that oneness.

00:37:54.840 --> 00:37:58.350
And these names are the names
of that place inside of us

00:37:58.350 --> 00:38:00.652
that is that.

00:38:00.652 --> 00:38:06.570
And as we chant these names,
or do these practices,

00:38:06.570 --> 00:38:09.595
what that inner essence
is covered with starts

00:38:09.595 --> 00:38:11.080
to dissolve.

00:38:11.080 --> 00:38:15.670
And that light, or that love, or
that truth, or that being that

00:38:15.670 --> 00:38:21.364
is who we really are, it starts
to become more available to us.

00:38:21.364 --> 00:38:22.840
So--

00:38:22.840 --> 00:38:24.808
[PLAYS HARMONIUM]

00:38:48.932 --> 00:38:50.640
I guess we're stick
here, because I can't

00:38:50.640 --> 00:38:53.190
think of anything to sing.

00:38:53.190 --> 00:38:57.142
What should we sing?

00:38:57.142 --> 00:38:59.118
[BAND DISCUSSING]

00:39:04.552 --> 00:39:11.100
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH] OK, so
I think this is on the sheet,

00:39:11.100 --> 00:39:14.170
radhe radhe govinda
bhaja govinda.

00:39:14.170 --> 00:39:19.370
"Bhaja" means to remember,
or to sing, or to praise.

00:39:19.370 --> 00:39:21.252
Don't eat that.

00:39:21.252 --> 00:39:22.155
[LAUGHTER]

00:39:22.155 --> 00:39:23.401
You can't eat that.

00:39:23.401 --> 00:39:25.990
It's not good for you.

00:39:25.990 --> 00:39:29.730
So I'm going to start with a
couple of verses in English.

00:39:29.730 --> 00:39:32.790
There was a great hymn written
many years ago by a great saint

00:39:32.790 --> 00:39:35.180
called Shankaracharya.

00:39:35.180 --> 00:39:37.670
He was walking down
the street one day.

00:39:37.670 --> 00:39:40.340
And he saw an old man
on the side of the road

00:39:40.340 --> 00:39:44.496
teaching rules of Sanskrit
grammar to some students.

00:39:44.496 --> 00:39:45.870
And being a great
saint, he could

00:39:45.870 --> 00:39:48.980
see that this old guy was
going to die very soon,

00:39:48.980 --> 00:39:50.840
and he'd never
done any practice,

00:39:50.840 --> 00:39:53.006
anything to help himself.

00:39:53.006 --> 00:39:54.630
So out of compassion,
he went up to him

00:39:54.630 --> 00:39:59.300
and he said, oh, my
friend, bhaja govinda.

00:39:59.300 --> 00:40:02.090
So "govinda" means
"Krishna," the name of God.

00:40:02.090 --> 00:40:05.430
And "bhaja" means "to sing
or praise or remember."

00:40:05.430 --> 00:40:09.200
So he's telling this guy, do
something before it's too late.

00:40:09.200 --> 00:40:10.430
And that night, he went home.

00:40:10.430 --> 00:40:14.410
And he wrote a long hymn that
he called "Bhaja Govinda."

00:40:14.410 --> 00:40:17.930
And each verse
describes the ways

00:40:17.930 --> 00:40:21.221
that we go through our lives
complete asleep, totally lost

00:40:21.221 --> 00:40:22.220
in whatever we're doing.

00:40:22.220 --> 00:40:23.180
And we never wake up.

00:40:23.180 --> 00:40:27.260
And we never do what's really
in our own best interests.

00:40:27.260 --> 00:40:29.192
And we don't get
the things we want.

00:40:29.192 --> 00:40:30.650
We don't get the
happiness we want.

00:40:30.650 --> 00:40:33.680
We don't find the love.

00:40:33.680 --> 00:40:36.230
And then the chorus at the
end of each verse went, "Oh,

00:40:36.230 --> 00:40:38.860
my foolish mind
or foolish heart."

00:40:38.860 --> 00:40:42.250
Bhaja govinda, do something.

00:40:42.250 --> 00:40:46.430
So I always wanted to read--
it's a beautiful poem.

00:40:46.430 --> 00:40:49.520
And I always wanted to
rewrite it with modern images

00:40:49.520 --> 00:40:55.220
because they didn't have
binge watching in 900,

00:40:55.220 --> 00:40:57.300
whenever Shankaracharya lived.

00:40:57.300 --> 00:41:00.710
That's how I waste
most of my time.

00:41:00.710 --> 00:41:03.196
But I'm too lazy,
and it's too long.

00:41:03.196 --> 00:41:04.320
And so that never happened.

00:41:04.320 --> 00:41:06.025
So I wrote a couple
of new verses--

00:41:06.025 --> 00:41:07.758
[PLAYS HARMONIUM]

00:41:07.758 --> 00:41:08.730
--in English.

00:41:12.140 --> 00:41:15.604
And then we'll sing radhe
radhe govinda bhaja govinda.

